Food was under cooked and didn't even have any of their own beers on tap.
By far the best bar in Coral Springs/Parkland - The vibe is always right and the beers+food are both always on point 🙏🏼

Large group of us after a funeral,  and i dont remember our waiters name, was a slim young guy, almost wanna say he had glasses, but maybe not.  He did a great job paying attention and expediting service to several people.
One of my main places to grab some food. excellent location, well organised, and awesome customer service. 5 stars!
Great local establishment with great food and drink selection. Even amidst restrictions, location was very clean, and sanitized. Excellent location for a quick bite and beverage!
Bartender made us some fabulous drinks
Overpriced, mediocre food coupled with slow service; don't bother!
The vibe here was super cool. I really loved it. Found it based on some Google searching. Good food. Good drinks
This place is amazing. Best atmosphere. Best food. Best drinks. Best service.  You won’t be let down dining here. I really enjoy coming here when I get off work.
Great beer selection , unique menu with tasty combinations and knowledgeable staff. A must to check out
Been there twice already and we love it! The atmosphere, the food and especially our bartender Michelle. She gave great recommendations on foods and her drinks are phenomenal!
Amaze balls
Very cool bar, cocktails, food and vibes are amazing. Wings were on point and the staff was awesome! Coming back for sure
Staff, management, drinks and food were all great, Love the vibe and atmosphere! Lobster Mac and cheese is bomb
Literally the worst.

We’ve been here a few times, burgers are decent but the service is hit or miss. One of the last time we called in an order and were told to call back because they were changing the oil in the fryer. So we waited then called in our order, went to pick up and waited another 30 minutes. The bar tender then realized that I was still waiting for my food. When they came out it was just burger and no fries because they still hadn’t figured out the oil. We like their burgers so we decided to give it another chance this past Sunday.... well I guess they just change the business hours as they please.... can’t do business if you can’t run a kitchen and you shut down when you feel like. My guess is this place won’t be around much longer if they can’t figure it out.
Beautiful bar. great beer and liquor selection. very friendly staff.
Good times Parkland Chamber of Commerce Holiday Party

This spot is my favored. I go to plenty of restaurants but to this place I  constantly return again and again. The crew is very attentive and the food they offer is so appetizing. I am always happy to have a decent meal here. I recommend this place with pleasure.

Fantastic place! The vibe, the different craft beer selection! And their chicken wings! Wow! Best I've had in the area! The staff really makes you have a great experience over all. Definitely coming back.
Dont bother, wont be back

Very kind and friendly staff. Burger and wings were good, but the fries were my favorite.  Will return...only downside was the metal chairs dont let my 40 something yr old butt sit very comfortably.  Glad they are here.

Awesome service-bartenders are extremely friendly and helpful . Nice vibe. Good music. Menu is changing so right now it’s not very extensive but the prices are ok. Food is great. Drinks are made a bit strong but I’m not complaining! If you are looking for a nice week day chill spot this place is perfect.

The worst food I had in a long time. I ordered $10 waffles, but what came to the table was 1 sorry, cold and moist waffle with few stale blueberries on time. Never again! This place won’t be open another 7 month with lack luster food and outrageous pricing.

Server was good, food was the worst I've ever had anywhere. Super overpriced. Belgian waffle was $10, and it was like the ones you make yourself at hotel lobbies, except worse because it was soggy and came out cold. My friends steak, which was a $25 plate, was raw and the outside looked grey like it was freezer burned. It was disgusting. The eggs weren't even cooked on the plate and the potatoes were all hard as a rock. When I explained to the server I couldn't eat my waffle she said because I had taken a bite she couldn't take it back. Waste of time and money. Don't come here. Oh and to add to the overpriced, unlimited mimosas are $25 and unlimited mules are $35.

As a regular patron of this establishment, I highly recommend going. They host a Dirty Bingo game every other Wednesday and it’s a blast. Also, the food is OD... I got the sliders last night and they were 👌🏽.
Chill spot, great craft beer selection, food and welcoming staff!

Nice time but VERY EXPENSIVE. $70 for happy hour drinks and 1 app. $11 for 1 draft beer 👀 no prices listed for drafts. When asked about the happy hour price they took off $2 from the bill...1 and done for me. Won't go back there.
The food's really good and the drinks are at a reasonable price and I love the workers will be going back soon
Great place to go and sample the different beers as well as the food the Chef puts together....
Knowledgeable friendly staff. Fantastic beer and spirits selection. Great food!
Hands down best bar in the area. Amazing staff, great food and not over priced. If any one is in the area I highly recommend it.
Good

Everything about the food was amazing :) staff and mgmt was A1, I mean I lived in Springs for 10 years and American Craft has been my go to spot for the year year or so. Trivia and Dorty Bingo are my fav 🤘🏽 The Tap spotlight are almost fun. Love this place

The food is good, if you can get it. They frequently run out of several items on their menu. The value for the portions is also poor, and the service is consistently slow or the staff is overwhelmed. If they could get their ordering, portions, and service in line, it would be a much better review.
Great service, decent food. The juciest wings.
Really cool vibe, over a dozen of their own, in-house brewed beers (only tried a few and ALL were spectacular), great service and the food was superb.  Highly-highly recommend this place!!!!

Ate a late dinner here last night with friends. Service was fantastic and food was amazing. We had the Shrimp and Grits. I have never had shrimp and grits that were so amazingly delicious. Bacon, sharp Vermont cheddar cheese, blue cheese, maple syrup, and scallions = heaven. Highly recommend!

This place was a joke.  The owner made me laugh. He wants an EXEC chef at 14 an hour, to work 35 hours a week, develop menus for him, and cost them out. So if ur EXEC chef is making 14 an hour, how good do u think the quality is gonna be?  Wish I could give zero stars. Food sucks, but drunk people don't know
The drinks were not made well and the overall environment was unappealing

Pretty cool place. The manager, Lee, knows how to make you feel welcome and genuinely wants everyone to enjoy the place. He truly cares about the customers experience and is always looking to improve. The beer is always excellent along with the alcohol selection. The bartenders def make a mean drink. the food selection has some good picks as well and they are always having new things on the menu. The whole staff is great and I highly recommend this spot.
Some of the best food in Coral Springs with out a doubt. Also great beer selections and full bar if not into craft beer
Come here all the time..Lee is the best! If you like craft beer this is a great local place to try.
Best place to hang out in town. Staff is super friendly, they make you feel like family. Make sure you get Karina, she's the best. Lee is second!
Best place to hang out!!! Lee is the best. Karina is second best.
Excellent selection of taps, friendly service with a smile and a menu with exciting specials. Bring some friends for trivia night or dirty bingo. 10/10.
Over priced drinks and mediocre menu.   Good beer list but pricey.

Saw an ad on FB for their GOT trivia and decided to give it a try. You had to make reservations so I was trying to call all day but no one picked up. Went out there and hoped for the best. My group was able to get a spot and the rest of the night was a blast. The tab will be high if you're there a while but that's most places like this.
The service was pretty good! 👍  i will visit you guys again!🍺
Great Craft beer selection!!!
Great food
Great little local place to grab a beer. Great service, selection and beer!

Lee was by far the best bartender/service employee I’ve ever come across. He took the time to know everyone’s name while I was here and used their names anytime speaking to them. This is including me. He didn’t just ask your name to be polite.  He remembered your name even though he was busy taking care of many others by himself at the bar. He was gracious and engaging in conversation when he had a moment. My wife works in the industry and I know what a great bartender looks like and Lee is absolutely it. While I can get beer many places, I can’t get many Lee’s so I will definitely be coming back for his incredible service alone.

Had a rough start trying to get reservations. No one would answer the phone, I had to use Facebook to make contact.  Once the reservations were straighten out we had a good time. I suggest that the prizes should go to the first person who tells bingo, not to everyone who has bingo. First up first to get prize.  Or first to get main prize and everyone else get some other type of prize like the drink coupons. Food was good and had a good time. Would definitely go back. Oh Yeah maybe some drink specials.
Great service!! Fun atmosphere !! Great place for live music also! Convenient next to movie theater!!
Great crowd and staff
Love everything about this bar! Food, beers and drinks were all great.
Shalom was a huge help! Looking forward to Dirty Bingo

Food for the adventerous. Great quality across the entire menu, with beer you'd rarely find anywhere else. Cool and cozy location.
This place became my all time favorite spot since it opened , the beer here is brewed just to my liking and i love bringing my GF and friends here with me.

We visited over the weekend for a friend's birthday. Great staff and beer selections. The staff was super friendly and the place was very clean!  Only thing that I would change is better placement and/or signage. We took an UBER there and passed it 2 times because there was no visible sign or store front from the road.

Great spot, new  , innovative and always fresh and upcoming , live music, great selection of drinks , greatatmoaphere.  I came with my girlfriend and am having a great time currently.  Haha I haven't even left yet and i had to write a quick review. Definitely get here. A great spot on any day or night

just went in for a drink and ended up making new friends. Great staff,  great drinks and awesome atmosphere
Great decor and atmosphere. The bar manager Lee and his staff will make you feel welcomed and help you have a great time. My new Sunday spot!!

Beer and food selection has really improved since I was last here a few months ago! Not just typical bar food and a cool space.
The good: friendly staff, trivia nights.  The not so good: craft beer selection and the food.  Need some work to be a “craft gastropub”.
We enjoyed our dinner.  I had chicken and bacon tacos.  They were excellent.  Hubby had grilled cheese.  A different menu!

Brass tap used to be a nice place to get a good bite and a drink before a flick. This was not. "Limited menu options" is an understatement. Beer picks were okay. Beyond overpriced. For $30 I got one beer and an undercooked burger. Will not be returning.

Used to be a fantastic place to experience a huge selection of Craft beers and have some pretty decent bar food. The bartenders were extremely well versed in the beers, very friendly and accommodating. They have some activities at night which can be fun. The biggest draw for my wife and I was Growler night, offering 50% off on Growler fills. This offered us the opportunity to take home hard to find quality beers at a good price. Unfortunately this is no longer offered and the beer selection has drastically dwindled with the selection of quality craft beers no longer a reason to frequent this establishment.
We stopped in for a late lunch. The menu was a bit bizzare and the service was a little slow but the food was okay. Won't rush back.
Ok

A nice place to get blasted before a movie. The menus were a bit messy like previous reviews stated, but the bar was staffed by 3 bartenders so it seems they got that sorted.  Drink selection is a bit limited, asked for a hurricane and they couldn't make it. I ordered the Bruce Banner and it was pretty good, had a lot of apple flavor so the squeeze of lime is more of a necessity than an extra. I also ordered the Weyerbacher Sunday Morning Stout which was VERY good, tastes a lot like coffee.  What we were told is Brass Tap was strict as a corporation and this location didn't have much of a say with beer and food picks so they may be in a transitional period. Full disclosure, we didn't order food so I have no clue how the experience is with that.

Walked in and walked out.  Beer listed on Instagram apparently only available at Boca location with none of their own beer available.  One server/ bartender working entire restaurant, draft list and food menu were abysmal.
Great live music. Good beer.
Last night was fun here, Cool vibes, good food and great staff plus dope band 🙌🏻
It was good
Decent.
Coral Springs was Ok. Small location.  They were out of some liquor despite having a full bar.  Small plates are innovative, like the chicken fried bacon & the avocado fries.
Awesome
Food was ok, if they have what you want. I went three times in three weeks and what I wanted to try they were always out of.

Tonight a group of friends and I went to enjoy an event that this establishment offered, the event was called "Dirty Bingo". While waiting for the event to start we ordered waters, during this time we glanced over the menu and began to order, the server explained that their menu is limited and they do not have all of the food offered on the menu. This made me very upset because we were not informed of the limited menu before or after being seated, furthermore the alcohol and food menus were both made of paper. I don't understand why their menu quality is the equivalent to what I could print out at home, many other bars in this area have nice high quality menus, while this bar does not. Now what made me the most upset is that another sever came up to us and said "Hey guys, you cannot be at this event if you don't order anything besides water" however the food I wanted to order was not available, due to the limited selection. Shortly after the announcer of the event reiterates over the microphone "that customers who do not order anything besides water can not participate in the event". Yes I do understand thier perspective it's no secret this is a business that is looking to make money, but I do not appreciate being called out over the intercom, seconds after the server walked away from our table, when I actually attempted to order two dishes - which they did not have either of the items I was asking to purchase. It was extremely disrespectful, and it's just simply bad business. I came in to have a good meal and enjoy a nice night out, but this company did not provide the items that were displayed in the menu as well as good service. They have now lost four customers, we will not be returning.

Nasty people, nasty place. We send our Tech to work on there electricity in order for them to open their business and it has been 137 days and they do not pay until now. It is always an excuse they are going to send a check until now the check can not reach.
username: D Electrician Technical Services Inc D

caption: Great food and craft beer. Highly recommended!!!

Very dirty restaurant. Floors not swept and menus covered in beer/food with many items crossed out because they are out of of half the stuff they sell. American Craft (formally Brass Tap) is continuing it’s downward spiral. Do yourself a favor and go somewhere else for craft beer and gastropub food.

Just ordered the Bacon and grilled cheese sandwhich with tomato soup. Absolutely disgusting!!! The bacon was literally nothing but chucks of fat. No meat at all. I’ve had plenty of bacon and grilled cheese sandwhiches that were tasty.. this one at American Craft was straight up disgusting. The tomato soup was just gross. Tasted almost rotton. I literally took a sip and nearly gagged! And I love tomato soup! How can they even call this tomato soup??  It’s unfortunate bc i work next door and it’s convenient to stay around here to buy lunch. But never ever again.  Huge waste of $11.
We attended this restaurant expecting a meal but were instead informed that there was no chef. This is a bar not a restaurant do not come expecting a meal.

I really want to like this place but I can't yet. We were there about 7pm on a Saturday before our movie. There were only about four customers in the restaurant when we arrived. We sat at the bar and were quickly greeted. The server gave us our menus. The first really big issue was the number of beers. They have 42 taps. The menu only had 29 draft beers on it and only 21 were available. So they were only offering half the number of beers that they could. I really wanted wanted to try something that I have not had. I did get something that I have not had but the choices were very limited. We ordered the tomato and mozzarella salad with the flight of filet. Both of these dishes were pretty tasty. The tomato and mozzarella salad had grape tomatoes and small mozzarella balls covered in a very tasty dressing. The flight of filet had three different 1/4 thick pieces of filet. One piece was coffe rubbed, one was pepper rubbed and the last was bacon wrapped. The coffee rubbed was the best tasting. The bacon wrapped was decent but the bacon was almost as large as the piece of filet. Another opportunity was the server telling me halfway thru my beer that today was manday. This ment whiskey and bourbons were two for one. If I would have known this at the beginning, I probably would have gone with that. The overall feel and look of the inside is nice and fits the idea of what they are trying to be. They have many promotions to bring customers in, from the many trivia nights. I want to give them another chance but they have a lot to fix in the beer choices, as this is what they are.
Great place to go for an awesome beer selection not seen in the area and live music as well! Taylor and Lee were my bartenders and they were absolutely amazing!!!

Such a tired concept and they dont even do it well. Food is baaaad. Better beer selections around town for cheaper too. Really no reason to come here. They rebranded and gave the place a facelift seemingly just to justify charging more. Dont waste your time
Loved the selection of brews! Taylor, the cutest, sweetest bartender ever, knew just what to recommend for each of our individual palates.

Worst service ever! The waiter was nice but was not attentive,  did not clean up once..ate dinner with dirty dishes and beverage cups, I had to go to the bar to order my drink that I ordered 10 mins prior..they didnt have any clean martini glasses..probably because there were so many tables with dirty dishes and cups all over and if they cleaned up they would have some...to top it off, i had a digital coupon to use and was told the manager was needed but he was on the ohone with his wife, we waited for 10 mins..I finally had enough..pay the entire amount in cash onky to see my waiter relaxing on the bar side being entertained & conversating the waiters as I walked up. Unbelievable! Will never come back amd will surely spread this to all our neighbors, friends and family to stay away from this Micky Mouse establishment.

We played here yesterday(Sunday) afternoon. We had lunch first and the food was great. The service was also great. We had alot of friends come watch us play and they were all very happy with the food and service.
My wife and I feel like we found a spot that fits us perfectly.. the beer selection is phenomenal, and everything is local. The menu is different then you are used to at a normal bar.

Servers here are BAD! Came in to meet some friends tonight Fri Jan 12th, 2018. Nobody even acknowledge me. I got up and ask one of the girls if somebody could come take my order, she came a few min later with some menus, I order a drink with her. About 10min later, I ask another server, he said you didn’t order with me, I said I know, but can you help me? He said sure after I take of my table.. Wow. What a great service. The only reason why  I’m giving 2 starts is because of Trivia night on Tuesday is fun. I had to go to Moon Thai for drinks, since I waited about 25 min... and my drink never arrived..

Been here twice since brass tap closed the food is mediocre. Ordered cheese sticks they were burned. Avocado fries were just battered and fried with no seasoning so very bland... our group could not eat it. also blt only had one piece of bacon.... I understand trying to make a profit but how can you mess up a blt? Anyway the drinks were twice as expensive as other local restaurants. I hope they turn this place around. Offer a $2 or $3 beer... Not $7 $10 beers only! 99% of there beers are $7 or more
